Article 5 (Retention, Processing Period, and Disposal of Personal Information)
1. Once the purpose of collection is fulfilled, your personal information is immediately disposed of by Olive Young. However, if longer retention is required by any applicable law or you agree to extended retention and processing period of your information, the data is securely stored and used only for the intended purposes.
1) If longer retention and processing period are required by applicable laws (not limited to followings).
- Record of Contracts and Subscription Withdrawal: 5 Years
- Record of Payment and Provision of Goods: 5 Years
- Record of Customer Complaint and Dispute Resolution: 3 Years
- Date and Time of Visit: 3 Months (Excluding the date and time of your last visit to confirm the period of service)
2) To minimize any loss or damages from repetitious account withdrawal and re-registration and to enable you to reactivate your account as required, your data will be destroyed immediately after your account is withdrawn.
3) Valid commercial credit (such as reward points) is retained until it expires.
2. Your information is disposed of or deleted by the following methods depending on its form.
1) Personal information stored on paper is shredded or incinerated.
2) Electronically stored personal information is securely disposed of and is not retrievable.
