Article 7 (Children's Privacy)
Our website is not intended for or directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information directly from children under the age of 13 without parental consent. If we become aware that a child under the age of 13 has provided us with personal information, we will delete the information from our records.
Article 8 (Additional Information for California Residents)
Based on CCPA, The California Privacy Rights Act of 2020 or “CPRA” (Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.100 et seq.) has strengthened regulations on business operators by expanding consumer’s right to privacy to be closer to the European Union’s GDPR.
If you reside in California, this section applies to you and describes our data practices today and in the preceding 12 months.
1. Categories of Personal Data
We collect the following categories of personal data: identifiers (such as your name, email, or IP address); commercial information (such as records of products you purchased); characteristics of protected classifications under California or U.S. federal law (such as your age or gender); internet or electronic network activity (such as information about your activity on our website); geolocation data (such as your city of residence); audio, electronic, visual, or similar information (such as phone recordings when you call our customer service channels); and inferences drawn from your personal data to create a profile (such as your shopping preferences). For examples of the precise data points we collect and the sources of such collection, please see the Information We Collect section above. We use personal data for the business or commercial purposes described in the Use of Information section above. We disclose personal data for the business purposes described in the Disclosure of Information section above. Additionally, in the preceding 12 months, we have disclosed the following categories of personal data for business purposes to the following categories of recipients:
Categories of Personal Data
Category of Personal Data
Categories of Recipients
Identifiers
Partners that provide advertising and marketing services, data analytics providers, payment processors, fulfillment partners, customer support partners, Internet service providers, operating systems and platforms, other users, cloud service providers, technical maintenance and system security providers
Commercial Information
Data analytics providers, partners that provide advertising and marketing services, payment processors, fulfillment partners, customer support partners, fraud prevention partners, and cloud service providers
