Article 14 (Matters on the operation of automatic collection devices and opt-out thereof)
1. Automatic Cookie collection
Olive Young uses collected ‘cookies’ to provide a more personalized experience on the website.
Cookies are small text files sent to your browser by the web server you visit and stored in the hard disk of your device (such as your desktop, smartphone, tablet PC, etc.) when you use services on Olive Young’s website or mobile app. Cookies identify the device you are using but not you as an individual. Cookies expire when you close the browser or sign out.
The data collected by cookies can be used for the following purposes:
1) To analyze the frequency and time of your visits, figure out your interests and patterns of use, and target your visits and events you participate in
2) To track your most viewed items and provide services tailored to your interests for a more personalized experience on the website
3) To analyze customer behavior for service improvement initiatives
You have a right to accept or disable cookies. You can accept all cookies, choose to be notified every time a cookie is issued, or disable all cookies.
Block/allow personalized ads via web browser
1) Internet Explorer (Internet Explorer 11 for Windows 10)
- In Internet Explorer, select the Tools button, then select Internet Options
- Select the Privacy tab, select Advanced under Settings, then Block or Allow Cookies
2) Microsoft Edge
- In Edge, click the "…" mark in the upper right corner, then click Settings.
- After clicking "Privacy, Search and Services" on the left side of the settings page, select whether to prevent tracking and the level in the [Tracking Prevention] section.
- Choose whether to “Always use ‘Strict’ Tracking Protection when browsing InPrivate.”
- In the [Privacy] section below, choose whether to “Send a ‘do not track’ request.”
3) Chrome
- In Chrome, click the top right "⋮" mark (Customize and control Chrome), then click the Settings.
- Click “Show advanced settings” at the bottom of the Settings page and click Content Settings in the [Privacy] section.
- In the Cookies section, check the box for “Block third-party cookies and site data.”
[Refusal Method]
- iOS: Home > Settings > Privacy > Tracking > Allow Apps to Request to Track (OFF)
- Android: Home > Settings > Google > Ads > Delete Advertising ID
※ The menu and methods are contingent upon the version of the mobile operating system.
2. Weblogs analytics using Google Analytics
CJ Olive Young Corporation uses Google Analytics, a weblog analysis tool provided by Google, Inc. (“Google”). Weblog analysis refers to the analysis of the customer’s use of website services. Google processes the information on behalf of CJ Olive Young Corporation and analyzes your website usage. CJ Olive Young Corporation does not process any personally identifiable information in this process. If you do not want Google to process your data, you can opt out of this by downloading and installing add-ons for your web browser at tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout.
[How to opt out]
- For Chrome: Click [Download Browser Add-on to block Google Analytics] > Click [Add to Chrome] > When pop-up window is displayed, click [Add Extension] > Click Done.
- For IE (Internet Explorer): Click [Download Browser Add-on to block Google Analytics] > Click [Agree and Install] > Click [Run] or [Save] on the window displayed at the bottom > Click [Restart Later] or [Restart Now], as the changed setting will only be applied after restarting the browser > Upon clicking [Restart Now], the pop-up on how to use the add-on will appear. Then, click [Use] > Done.
For more information on Google Analytics’ processing of information, please visit support.google.com/analytics/answer/6004245
If you want to stop log analysis through an external analysis tool, you can cancel the setting through the guidance page below.
https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/181881?hl=en
